36. And Joses. Joses, Josetus, Josephus, and Joseph are one and the same name, with various terminations, as Drusius, Grotius, and others observe.

lVlzo was sur-named Barnabas. This surname is a Syriae com- position, from the name Bar and Nabia, or by abridgment Naba, the third person of the future of the verb bia, “to comfort-’⁹ And thus Bar-naba signifieth “the comforting son ;” the Hebrews and Syrians using often the future for the present participle, as Lud. de Dieu observes. Nor was this surname given him by the common people, but by the apostles themselves, which redounded to his greater praise. The names which were given to the apostles by Christ did not want a happy portending3 nor did they doubtless want the same which were given to others by the apostles, being filled with the Holy Ghost.
